benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/simplePlan - Add a simple plan entry in the current version of the catalog

covered: POST Valid Payload: TC01 covers creation with valid payload, returns HTTP 201, and ensures the new plan is retrievable in the catalog
POST Invalid Payload: TC04, TC08, TC09 cover missing headers, empty body, and malformed JSON
POST Duplicate Submission: TC06 covers duplicate planId handling
POST Large Payloads: TC15 covers handling of very large payloads
POST Validation: TC05 (invalid currency), TC12 (maximum field lengths), TC13 (minimum field values), TC18 (XSS/SQL injection patterns) cover input validation and security considerations
POST Authorization: TC10 covers 401 for missing authentication
POST Unsupported HTTP Method: TC14 covers 405 for unsupported method
POST System Availability: TC11 covers 503 when the catalog service is unavailable
POST Network Resilience: TC16 covers recovery from temporary network failure
POST Performance: TC17 covers response time within acceptable threshold
POST Catalog State: TC19 (empty catalog) and TC20 (partially populated) cover catalog state edge cases
Backward Compatibility: TC21 covers compatibility with previous API clients
Integration: TC23 and TC24 cover integration with dependent catalog services
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling for POST not explicitly tested
Caching headers verification (ETag, Cache-Control) for POST responses
500 Internal Server Error scenario not explicitly tested (503 is covered for service unavailability)
403 Forbidden boundary for authorization not tested
recommendations: Add a 500 Internal Server Error test case for POST to cover server-side failures
Add a 403 Forbidden test case to validate authorization boundaries beyond 401
Add rate-limiting tests for POST to verify throttling behavior under load
Add tests to verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on POST responses
Add an explicit GET-after-create verification to robustly prove retrievability
Expand boundary-case payload tests to include cross-field validation and more extreme values
